There is panic as gunmen suspected to be armed robbers and kidnappers have taken over some communities in Akwa Ibom State. A Catholic priest, identified as Alphonsus Uboh was abducted in the church premises.  According to the witness,  the incident occurred after a similar one within the community, where the Founder and President of Solid Rock Kingdom Church was abducted from his residence, but later regained freedom after spending four days in the kidnappers’ den .
  
The affected communities include; villages along Ekparakwa/Ikot Abasi road in OrukAnam  Local Council  and Ikot Ebak, Ikot Akaam, Ibekwe Akpan axis in Mkpat Local  Council.
   
It was gathered that residents  in the  area and other surrounding villages in  OrukAnam and Mkpat Enin were being  robbed daily,  while others are kidnapped for ransom.
    
A youth leader, who spoke to newsmen on the condition of anonymity in  Ekparakwa on Sunday, said more than 18 people were abducted between November 2021 and April, adding that the area  is no  more safe at the moment.  The Police Public Relations Officer, Odiko Mcdon, who confirmed abduction of the Catholic Priest and other activities of gunmen in the area in a telephone call, promised to track the criminals. 